text: FTP and SFTP servers are allowed by the University firewall
The system passively monitors the network throughput when traffic is light
SMTP is allowed by the University firewall
Guests cannot run any file sharing/downloading program

If a student is in obvious violations of copyright law by using a room's wired connection (ie ResNet) to distribute copyrighted materials, the room's connection will be disabled, and the issue could be sent to Housing Student Judicial Affairs
AIM chat and file transfering is allowed by the University firewall
Sorenson Videophone 200 is allowed by the University firewall
There is a 6 GB per 24-hour period upload or download data transfer limit starting at midnight of each day, on all of your combined traffic on ResNet and UIC wireless
Faculty members have 500 Gb per week of free network use
RHIT-OPEN will work in labs, classrooms and residence halls but does not allow the user to access the internal Rose-Hulman network
The UVA More Secure Network uses a firewall, a network security device designed to help protect your computer from hackers and other malicious people on the Internet.
The network firewall does prevent some applications from working in their normal manner, for example, video and audio conferencing products that use the H.323
